Cranberry Pistachio Energy Bars

1 c uncooked old-fashioned rolled oats
3/4 c uncooked quinoa
3/4 c dried cranberries, coarsley chopped (can sub any dried fruit)
1/2 c salted, dry-roasted pistachios, chopped (can sub any nuts)
1/3 c flaked unsweetened coconut
2 tbsp flax meal
1 oz bittersweet chocolate, finely chopped
1/2 c unsalted creamy almond butter
6 tbsp agave nectar (or honey)
1 tbsp canola oil
1/4 tsp salt
cooking spray

Preheat oven to 350F. Spread oats and quinoa on a baking sheet. Bake for 8 min or until lightly browned. Cool. Place oat mixture in a large bowl and stir in fruit, nuts, coconut, flax meal, and chocolate. Combine almond butter, agave, oil, and salt in a small saucepan over medium heat; bring to a boil. Cook 1 min, stirring constantly. Pour mixture over oat mixture, toss well to coat. Press mixture into a 8" square glass/ceramic baking dish coated with non-stick cooking spray. Bake at 350F for 13 min or until lightly browned. Completely cool in dish. Cut evenly into 1x4" bars.
